 10  /-- `ℕ+` is the type of positive natural numbers. It is defined as a subtype,
 11    and the VM representation of `ℕ+` is the same as `ℕ` because the proof
 12    is not stored. -/

162  /-- We define m % k and m / k in the same way as for nat
163    except that when m = n * k we take m % k = k and
164    m / k = n - 1.  This ensures that m % k is always positive
165    and m = (m % k) + k * (m / k) in all cases.  Later we
166    define a function div_exact which gives the usual m / k
167    in the case where k divides m.
168  -/
